parameters: Poso: "Hah hah... damn it... she didn't wake up again today..."
My cock... can't even make Umi regain consciousness...
Poso: "Seriously... she's not waking up at all..."
Poso: "Hey Umi, it's about time to wake up..."
Poso: "This is odd... she's never this hard to wake up... Is her heart?!"

Poso: "Thank goodness... it's beating... but... it's strange that she won't
wake up... maybe the drug was too strong..."
Poso: "Yes, I'm here... what do you need...?"

Soldier: "No, no... the shrine maiden has gone missing... we're searching
for her. You haven't seen her, have you?"
Poso: "Eh! That is... I don't know... she's missing?"

Soldier: "Yeah... well, she's probably gone off to the forest or the
kingdom or something... let me know if you find her."
Poso: "This is bad... what should I do..."
And so, Umi never woke up...

It was probably a side effect of the drug... I became terrified and carried
Umi to my house's basement to hide her.

The village was in an uproar, and the villagers and soldiers were
frantically searching everywhere for Umi. I joined in the search, knowing
full well she wasn't there, but I pretended to look desperately.

As a result of Umi's disappearance, the villagers were forced to take
responsibility. One by one, they were executed at intervals.

One person was killed every week. I was spared for the time being because I
had a shop.

I wonder what I should have done... should I have been honest at that
time...
Poso: "Hey Umi... what should I have done, huh?"
Poso: "Because of my cowardice, everyone in the village got involved..."
Poso: "It's not my fault... no... I'm not to blame..."
Poso: "It's that drug... the effects of that oil are to blame..."

Poso: "No... if Chancellor Shif hadn't come to this village... if Banka
hadn't betrayed us, none of this would have happened..."

Poso: "No... if Kru had never come to this village, Umi and I would have
naturally ended up together..."

Poso: "That's right! It must be! It's decided! It's all his fault! He's to
blame for everything!"
I no longer have any sensation...
The sensation of breathing, of light, of sound, of heat...
But, that this has happened is this man's fault...
This man and I are to blame...
So... it's better to just disappear...
To be burned by the hellfire and vanish...
That would be at least some atonement... My last struggle...
